entry.title: [Promise Icons] Allow promise icons for reinstalled apps
entry.content:
Previously there was a bug where installing, uninstalling then

reinstalling an app would only create a promise icon when the app was

installed for the first time, but never for subsequent installations.

To fix that, this CL expands the check for a new app installation to

consider the various “uninstalled” statuses that apps can have while

registered in the AppRegistryCache. This will enable the installation

to be considered valid and eligible for a promise icon.

entry.title: Refactor externally managed installation flow
entry.content:
This CL has two main goals:

* Improving the readability of the installation flow and making

future changes easier to implement (DD [1]).

* Enabling in-place update of placeholder apps (DD [2]).



This is done by eliminating the split between installation tasks

and commands. This CL introduces a core `ExternalAppResolutionCommand`

command that is scheduled with a minimal lock when an externally

managed app should be installed. It loads all metadata and acquires

additional locks as needed and delegates functionality to sub jobs.

This part of the change implements no functionality change.



The 2nd part of this change implements in-place updates of placeholder

apps by checking in the `ExternalAppResolutionCommand` whether the app

id has changed and performs a migration if that is the case.



[1] https://docs.google.com/document/d/1B0HqAhv1nPq75qOtFtKNIiDrS0QjFUrYA3cKMONlRKE/edit?resourcekey=0-C053as2pQ5cdK_ixjTbw_Q#heading=h.5svp30dzbfrh

entry.title: Revert "[//cc] Add MappableSI path to OneCopyRasterBufferProvider"
entry.content:
This reverts commit 031f7c9ee19d8524abd7a1351b2e10de44ac78bf.



Reason for revert: Might cause a test consistency failure on https://ci.chromium.org/ui/p/chromium/builders/luci.chromium.ci/chromeos-amd64-generic-rel



Apologize for reverting. Please feel free to reland if it is not related, thanks.



Original change's description:

> [//cc] Add MappableSI path to OneCopyRasterBufferProvider

>

> This CL adds a new path to OneCopyRasterBufferProvider that uses

> MappableSharedImage rather than GpuMemoryBuffer. The new path is

> protected by a killswitch. The gist of the change is that rather than

> creating a GpuMemoryBuffer, mapping that in, and then later creating a

> SharedImage from it, the new path directly creates a

> MappableSharedImage (via the new CreateSI() entrypoint), maps that in,

> *and* additionally uses it in the same ways that the SI created from

> the GMB is being used.

>

> One subtlety is that the GMB is created with the size of the

> StagingBuffer, while the SharedImage for the StagingBuffer in its

> current creation point in CopyOnWorkerThread() is created with the

> `resource_size` param passed to PlaybackAndCopyOnWorkerThread(). Thus,

> we would want the MappableSI for the StagingBuffer to be created with

> "both" sizes. Fortunately (and as one would expect), the StagingBuffer

> is initialized with the `resource_size` param, so the two sizes are

> guaranteed to be the same [1].

>

> [1] https://source.chromium.org/chromium/chromium/src/+/main:cc/raster/one_copy_raster_buffer_provider.cc;l=295-297?q=CopyOnWorker&ss=chromium
